					<div class="commentheading">On June 07, 2006 at 12:59 PM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Sirloin tip</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Quote:<div class='commentquotebody'>This end is referred to as the small end rib roast or loin rib roast or sirloin tip roast. </div></div><br />
<br />
The sirloin tip roast (AKA round tip roast, AKA beef knuckle) is cut from the front of the leg, the area from the hip to the knee. It is not associated with the rib.</div>
