					<div class="commentheading">On June 15, 2007 at 04:34 PM, Libra (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>prime rib roast</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I let roast rise to room temp on the counter.  Slightly dampen the outside then roll in rock salt.  Pat it on like a shell.  Add coarse ground black pepper to shell.  Place in oven at 450 degrees for 15 or so minutes.  Turn oven down to 200 and roast til meat thermometer is at desired temp.  Quicker and easier than browning  in the pan.  It browns in hot oven and salt seals in juices.  To serve, break away salt shell.</div>
