					<div class="commentheading">On December 29, 2007 at 02:58 AM, Sillyboy (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>My Experience</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Since I benefited from others experiences, thought I would add my own:<br />
<br />
10 lb prime rib<br />
<br />
1 hr at room temp<br />
preheat to 450 deg<br />
lower to 200 when roast is inserted.<br />
<br />
0.0hr 39 <br />
1.0hr 46<br />
2.0hr 68<br />
3.0hr 92<br />
4.0hr 112<br />
4.5hr 120, temp increase to 220.<br />
5.0hr 127 <br />
5.5hr 135, removed, start resting.<br />
6.0hr 140<br />
<br />
(33 minutes per pound)<br />
<br />
30 minute rest.<br />
<br />
I would call it ... med-well side of medium.  More than I hoped, but edible at least, which is good for me :)<br />
<br />
quite a bit of juice (~1 cup) "leaked" out during slicing.  Hard to quantify, but easily a cup.  I suspect a long rest would have helped there.</div>
