					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On December 23, 2010 at 06:04 PM, DeAnna (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>pre-cooked prime rib</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Yes the whole roast has been pre-cooked and frozen and yes it's de-thawing now.  Some people suggested for reheating slices to place romaine lettuce over the slices and reheat in the oven.  I'm less concerned with the time it takes as long as I don't overcook the thing.  The supplier said he left it in the bag and put the whole thing in the microwave one time for 7  minutes but I'm not sure I want to try that.  Possibly if I just bring it to room temperature and slice it and pour hot jus over it it would work just as well.  Thanks</div>
