					<div class="commentheading">On November 25, 2012 at 02:19 PM, Canuk Bill (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Bladed or mechanically tenderized cuts</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Costco Canada along with some other retailers has recently added a notice to almost all of their beef roasts and steaks stating that they have been mechanically tenderized or 'bladed' and recommends that they be cooked to an internal temperature of 160'F or 71'C. This follows a CBC consumer report on the meat retail industry showing that most cuts are processed in this way and may have surface bacteria transferred to the inside. As a person who had previously thought that cooking the outside of a cut above 160' would make it safe, this is disturbing to say the least. :angry:</div>
