					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I did an office party dinner once for like 40 people - used multiple 10 lb roasts - I think it is a bit easier to manage than one large.<br />
<br />
obviously having two roasts would make the medium/medium rare thing much easier - you can simply start one about an hour earlier than the medium rare.  <br />
<br />
it also depends on the projected quantity of each you may need - i.e. typically the ends of the roast are more medium than m-rare, to a depth of perhaps 3/4-1 inch.  however if half the crowd wants medium, you'll need more medium than that.</div>
